solution:
You nailed it! Your policy should prevent anyone from accessing the sensitive files before the information is officially made public.
Now, this situation is a bit more complex compared to the previous ones.
However, your solution may resemble the one outlined below:

```json
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "s3:GetObject",
        "s3:ListBucket"
      ],
      "Principal": {
        "AWS": "*"
      },
      "Resource": [
        "arn:aws:s3:::acme-earnings-calls",
        "arn:aws:s3:::acme-earnings-calls/*"
      ]
    },
    {
      "Effect": "Deny",
      "Action": [
        "s3:GetObject"
      ],
      "Principal": {
        "AWS": "*"
      },
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::acme-earnings-calls/2025/04/*",
      "Condition": {
        "DateLessThan": {
          "aws:CurrentTime": "2025-04-07T13:00:00Z"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "Effect": "Deny",
      "Action": [
        "s3:ListBucket"
      ],
      "Principal": {
        "AWS": "*"
      },
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::acme-earnings-calls",
      "Condition": {
        "DateLessThan": {
          "aws:CurrentTime": "2025-04-07T13:00:00Z"
        },
        "StringLike": {
          "s3:prefix": "2025/04/*"
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

However, there was another option to rely on numbers rather than dates.
Converting the date *2025-04-07T13:00:00Z* to a Unix epoch number yields a value of `1744030800`,
which can later be compared to the current epoch time. Please see the example below.

```json
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "s3:GetObject",
        "s3:ListBucket"
      ],
      "Principal": {
        "AWS": "*"
      },
      "Resource": [
        "arn:aws:s3:::acme-earnings-calls",
        "arn:aws:s3:::acme-earnings-calls/*"
      ]
    },
    {
      "Effect": "Deny",
      "Action": [
        "s3:GetObject"
      ],
      "Principal": {
        "AWS": "*"
      },
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::acme-earnings-calls/2025/04/*",
      "Condition": {
        "NumericLessThanEquals": {
          "aws:EpochTime": "1744030800"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "Effect": "Deny",
      "Action": [
        "s3:ListBucket"
      ],
      "Principal": {
        "AWS": "*"
      },
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::acme-earnings-calls",
      "Condition": {
        "NumericLessThanEquals": {
          "aws:EpochTime": "1744030800"
        },
        "StringLike": {
          "s3:prefix": "2025/04/*"
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

Take a break, relax, and when you're ready, let's continue to the next challenge.
